  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Local Resilience and Early Recovery for Typhoon Odette-Affected Communities through Durable Shelter Solutions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to promote early recovery for the communities worst affected by Typhoon Rai in Dinagat Islands and Surigao del Norte, in the Philippines, while strengthening their resilience to future disasters. In particular, the International Organization for Migration (IOM) will support their access to dignified and durable shelter solutions &#x2013; typhoon resilient shelter consisting of a hardened unit, &#x201C;safe room (panic room)&#x201D; &#x2013; that can provide life-saving protection from extreme weather events. Combined with capacity building support on disaster preparedness and management, the project will contribute to a more resilient community with increased capacity to withstand disasters and bounce back from crises.</narrative>
  </description>
